cc @Naveen @Mohit

I thought we had fixed Try It.

@Ashish @Nithin @Martin Xu, the `Try It` functionality is fixed on prod/dogfood, from 22.06, however you will not be able to use `Try It` feature for models trained prior to that. IF you want to enable `Try it` for a marketplace app consuming model service, you would need to retrain it on latest release to work!
Please note that if you’re using any UDF with ibfile APIs in solution, we recommend using `read_file` function instead of `ibopen` since `ibopen` doesn’t support in memory processing for `Try It`.
